article.headline: N. Arizona 68, Texas-Pan American 55
article.story: FLAGSTAFF, Ariz. -- Cameron Jones scored a season-high 27 points and Northern Arizona extended its longest winning streak in five seasons with a 68-55 victory over Texas-Pan American on Wednesday night. Jones scored 17 points in the final 17 minutes as the Lumberjacks (7-2) broke open a close game in the second half and cruised to their seventh straight win. It's Northern Arizona's longest winning streak since notching 10 in a row during the 2005-06 season. Gabe Rogers scored eight points -- all in the second half -- and Shane Johannsen grabbed 10 rebounds for Northern Arizona, which held a 40-28 rebounding advantage. Perry Petty scored 13 points for the Broncs (3-7), who fell to 0-4 all time against Northern Arizona.
